data.name: label1.Text
data.value: Note, FieldWorks will not make any changes to the standard format files you are importing.

data.name: lblBackupInstructions.Text
data.value: Backup the FieldWorks project before importing. Then, if you are not satisified with the results of the import, you can restore the backup to undo the import.

data.name: lblOverviewInstructions.Text
data.value: This procedure will help you supply the settings needed to be able to import your standard format lexical data.

data.name: lblSaveAsInstructions.Text
data.value: Your import settings will be saved to this file, for use in any future imports.

data.name: lblSettingsInstructions.Text
data.value: Select an import settings file. You will be able to modify/customize these settings to fit the database you're importing.

data.name: lblDatabaseInstructions.Text
data.value: Specify the standard format file containing the lexical data you want to import into FieldWorks.

data.name: lblMappingLanguagesInstructions.Text
data.value: Specify the languages used in {0}, and which FieldWorks Writing Systems they map to:

data.name: lblContentInstructions2.Text
data.value: If you cannot find a good match, you can bring the text into an "import residue" field of the Lexical Entry or Sense.

data.name: lblContentInstructions1.Text
data.value: Now tell FieldWorks how to import each field in your Standard Format dictionary.

data.name: labelStep5Description.Text
data.value: FieldWorks needs to know which standard format marker(s) begin a group of related fields. Select at least one marker for each group. By selecting more than one marker, a new group will be started for any of these markers that have already occurred in the current group. A checked marker can only occur once in a given group. Click Help for examples.

data.name: label2.Text
data.value: Indicate any markup you have used in your data to identify character styles, writing systems, or direct formatting.

data.name: lblGenerateReportMsg.Text
data.value: A report will be opened in your web browser.

data.name: FeasabilityCheckInstructions.Text
data.value:
In this step, FieldWorks will do a trial run of interpreting the dictionary you are importing using the mapping you have set up. It will produce a "readiness report" (which is currently rather scary) telling you what it found.
If the results are not satisfactory, you can press "Back" and modify some settings. You may also need to edit the file you are importing. Then proceed back to this screen and generate a new readiness report.
When you are satisfied and ready to proceed with the import, click "Next".

data.name: lblFinishWOImport.Text
data.value: Finish with out importing. Useful for creating all of the phaseXoutput files and related files.

data.name: lblReadyToImportInstructions.Text
data.value:
You are now ready to import your data into FieldWorks.
To begin importing, click Finish.
